law.text:
The purposes of the Program include:
providing information and helping consumers with the procedures for filing a complaint with the Commissioner against any person regulated by this article;
on request, giving information about an insurer to the extent that the information lawfully is disclosable; and
developing an information and assistance system to provide information about and to help consumers with:
personal insurance coverages, including health insurance and life insurance coverages;
underwriting practices;
general rating concepts;
claim procedures of insurers; and
any other relevant services.
